======================================================================
THE DIHEDRAL LADDER — FULL SPECTRAL ANALYSIS
======================================================================

SECTION 1: EVEN n CIRCULANT TOURNAMENT IMPOSSIBILITY
--------------------------------------------------
For even n, element n/2 is self-paired (n/2 = n - n/2).
This forces bidirectional or missing edge => no tournament.
  n=2: element 1 is self-paired. D_{4} acts on 2-gon but NO circulant tournament exists.
  n=4: element 2 is self-paired. D_{8} acts on 4-gon but NO circulant tournament exists.
  n=6: element 3 is self-paired. D_{12} acts on 6-gon but NO circulant tournament exists.
  n=8: element 4 is self-paired. D_{16} acts on 8-gon but NO circulant tournament exists.


